('7411', '1', 'Prepare an ice-water bath. set aside.'),
('7411', '2', 'Place a dozen eggs in a saucepan large enough to hold them in a single layer. cover with cold water by 2 inches. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, and simmer 1 1/2 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer eggs to the ice-water bath, and let cool. Meanwhile, repeat with remaining eggs. Peel eggs, dipping them in cold water if needed to remove shell pieces. (Peeled eggs can be refrigerated in an airtight container overnight.)'),
('7412', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (205 degrees C). Lightly oil a 9x13 inch baking dish. Season the trout inside and out with salt and pepper to taste, and place in baking dish.'),
('7412', '2', 'In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, olive oil, 2 tablespoons chopped parsley, and minced garlic.'),
('7412', '3', 'Spread evenly over the fish.'),
('7412', '4', 'Bake for 35 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.  Baste during baking with wine.'),
('7412', '5', 'Serve garnished with lemon wedges and parsley sprigs.'),
('7414', '1', 'Heat 1/2 cup vegetable oil in small saucepan over high heat.'),
('7414', '2', 'Add shallots and cook until golden brown and crisp, about 10 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer fried shallots to paper towels to drain.'),
('7414', '3', 'Grind peppercorns and star anise to powder in spice grinder.'),
('7414', '4', 'Transfer ground spices to mini processor.'),
('7414', '5', 'Add cilantro stems, garlic, and ginger. grind to paste. Set spice paste aside.'),
('7414', '6', 'Place pork in medium bowl.'),
('7414', '7', 'Place bowl on steamer rack in pot. Cover pot and steam pork over high heat until tender, about 20 minutes. Cool. cut into 1/2-inch pieces.'),
('7414', '8', 'Heat remaining 1/4 cup oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.'),
('7414', '9', 'Add steamed pork and saut until crisp, about 10 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer pork to clean bowl.'),
('7414', '10', 'Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat from skillet and add spice paste. Cook over medium-high heat until beginning to brown and crisp, about 2 minutes.'),
('7414', '11', 'Mix in palm sugar, then 1/3 cup water and fish sauce. Stir until palm sugar melts and caramelizes, about 5 minutes.'),
('7414', '12', 'Add remaining 1/3 cup water and boil until sauce thickens and coats spoon, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.'),
('7414', '13', 'Mix in pork. do ahead Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate pork. Cover shallots and store at room temperature.'),
('7414', '14', 'Add shallots to pork and warm over medium heat before using.'),
('7415', '1', 'Using a sharp knife, peel the bitter white pith from the oranges and lemon. be sure to remove all of the pith. Working over a bowl, cut in between the membranes to release the sections.'),
('7415', '2', 'Add the grated orange and lemon zests, olives, parsley, garlic, olive oil and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper and toss gently.'),
('7415', '3', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the vegetable oil. Season the trout fillets with salt and pepper and dust with flour.'),
('7415', '4', 'Add the trout to the skillet and cook over moderately high heat until browned on the bottom, about 2 minutes. Turn the fillets, reduce the heat to moderate and cook until just white throughout, about 3 minutes.'),
('7415', '5', 'Transfer the fillets to plates or a platter, spoon the relish on top and serve.'),
('7418', '1', 'In a stock pot heat oil over medium-high heat. Cook onion, garlic, fennel seed and potatoes and saute forabout 5 minutes.'),
('7418', '2', 'Add paprika, water and stir.'),
('7418', '3', 'Add fish and thyme and bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 15-20 minutes.Puree the tomatocan and add to the pot, add soy sauce, pepper and salt and simmer for 5 more minutes.'),
('7418', '4', 'Add orange juice and celery leaves simmer 2 more minutes and remove from heat.'),
('7418', '5', 'Serve hot with lemon wedges and freshly baked onion bread.'),
('7419', '1', 'Using vegetable peeler, shave carrots andcucumber lengthwise into ribbons.'),
('7419', '2', 'Cutribbons into 3-inch-long sections, then cutsections into matchstick-size strips.'),
('7419', '3', 'Placein large bowl.'),
('7419', '4', 'Add shallots, jalapenos, limejuice, sugar, and fish sauce. let marinate 30minutes at room temperature.'),
('7419', '5', 'Add trout pieces and tomatoes tovegetable mixture and toss to blend.'),
('7419', '6', 'Transfer trout-vegetable mixture to largestrainer and drain off liquid. Return trout-vegetablemixture to same bowl. add mintand basil and toss to blend.'),
('7419', '7', 'Arrange lettuce leaves on large platter.Divide trout-vegetable salad among lettuceleaves.'),
('7419', '8', 'Drizzle sweet chili sauce over eachsalad and sprinkle with peanuts.'),
('7419', '9', '* Available in the Asian foods section of most supermarkets, at some specialty foods stores, and at Asian markets.'),
('7419', '10', '** Available at some supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and delicatessens.'),
('7419', '11', '***Available at some supermarkets and at Asian markets and from amazon.com.'),
('7420', '1', 'Peel and chop the potatoes and boil them in water until cooked. Then mash them and leave them to cool until they are completely cold.Chop the ginger, chilli, lemon grass and coriander. Peel and finely chop the garlic.Flake the crab and the smoked trout into a large mixing bowl.Gently fry the garlic in olive oil for 1 minute, set to one side to cool.Put all of the ingredients (except for the ingredients for the coating) into the mixing bowl with the fish and mix it all together so that it is evenly distributed.Shape the mixture into round cakes, either by hand or by filling a pastry cutter. Then chill them in the fridge for at least an hour (they need to be firm enough to handle).'),
('7420', '2', 'Heat the oven to 180c.'),
('7420', '3', 'Put the flour for the coating onto a plate, put the beaten egg into a dish and put the breadcrumbs onto another plate.One at a time, carefully roll each of the fish cakes in the flour...... then coat them in the the beaten eggs...... and finally roll them in the breadcrumbs.'),
('7420', '4', 'Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium-high heat and then fry the fish cakes on both sides until thay are golden.'),
('7420', '5', 'Transfer the fish cakes to a baking tray and put them into the oven for 6 minutes.'),
('7420', '6', 'Remove the fish cakes from the oven and allow them to rest for 5 minutes before serving. We served them with a mixed leaf salad and mayonnaise mixed with lemon juice and 1 teaspoon of wasabi.'),
('7421', '1', 'Stir together all ingredients and a pinch of salt.'),
('7422', '1', 'Overlap fish on one side of platter.'),
('7422', '2', 'Whisk oil and lemon juice in bowl. Season dressing with salt and pepper. Toss half with fennel and half with arugula. Mound both alongside fish. Sprinkle with chives.'),
('7423', '1', 'Place eggs in a single layer in a saucepan. cover with water. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to low and cook at the barest simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('7423', '2', 'Remove from heat, pour out hot water and run a constant stream of cold water over the eggs until completely cooled.Nutrition'),
