('7424', '1', 'Place the salt and water into a 4-quart container and stir until the salt has dissolved, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('7424', '2', 'Add the trout filets, making sure they are submerged. Cover and refrigerate overnight.'),
('7424', '3', 'Combine water, vinegar, sugar, cloves, allspice, peppercorns, bay leaves, and red pepper flake in a 2-quart saucepan set over medium high heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the liquid comes to a boil, approximately 5 minutes. Cool to room temperature and then refrigerate overnight.'),
('7424', '4', 'Remove the trout from the brine and rinse thoroughly under cold running water for 1 minute. Submerge the filets in clean cold water and refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('7424', '5', 'Drain and rinse the filets. Pat dry. Lay the filets in a single layer, skin side down and brush each with mustard.'),
('7424', '6', 'Place a cornichon or a pickled onion on the filet.'),
('7424', '7', 'Roll up each filet and secure with 1 or 2 toothpicks. Alternate layers of rollmops and julienned onion in a glass jar or ceramic crock.'),
('7424', '8', 'Pour on the chilled pickling mixture, cover and refrigerate for at least 5 hours and up to 2 days.'),
('7424', '9', 'Drain and serve chilled with crusty bread.'),
('7427', '1', 'Mix first 4 ingredients in bowl. Gradually whisk in oil.'),
('7427', '2', 'Mix in capers, chopped dill and generous amount of pepper. (Can be made 3 days ahead. Cover. chill.)'),
('7427', '3', 'Line large platter with lettuce. Arrange smoked fish atop lettuce.'),
('7427', '4', 'Garnish with lemon and dill sprigs.'),
('7427', '5', 'Serve fish with bread and sauce.'),
('7428', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F. Wrap tortillas in foil. place in oven 10 minutes. Arrange tortillas on work surface. Press 2 tablespoons filling for corn or 3 tablespoons filling for flour tortillas into 3- to 4-inch strip on bottom third of each tortilla.'),
('7428', '2', 'Roll up. secure with toothpicks.'),
('7428', '3', 'Pour oil into large skillet to depth of 1 inch. Attach deep-fry thermometer. heat oil to 350F. Fry floutas 3 or 4 at a time until golden, turning occasionally, about 4 minutes. Using tons, hold flautas vertically over skillet to drain off oil. transfer to paper towels to drain.'),
('7428', '4', 'Remove toothpicks.'),
