('7429', '1', 'Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat.'),
('7429', '2', 'Line the cavity of the fish with slices of garlic, and slices of lemon. Stuff the fresh basil and rosemary inside. Season with salt and pepper. Wrap the fish in foil, and set on wire rack over a campfire, or on the grill.'),
('7429', '3', 'Cook for 15 to 20 minutes over direct heat, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('7429', '4', 'Remove herbs and lemon from the fish. Hold the fish up by its spine, and comb the meat from the bones using a fork.'),
('7429', '5', 'Serve with lemon wedges for squeezing over fish.'),
('7430', '1', 'Peel the potatoes, cut into quarters, and boil in salty water until tender.'),
('7430', '2', 'Drain the potatoes and beat with the butter, either by hand or using a mixer.'),
('7430', '3', 'In the meantime, remove any skin or bone from the fillets and roughly break up the flesh.  Cover with boiling water and let them sit for ten minutes to soften.'),
('7430', '4', 'Fold the fish, along with the dill and salt and pepper to taste, into the warm potatoes.  Allow to cool a little, then shape into 10-12 patties, each with a chunk about the size of a large golf ball.'),
('7430', '5', 'Lay out the patties on a cutting board and dust with a sprinkling of flour.'),
('7430', '6', 'Heat the oil over medium-high heat in a skillet (or two to expedite frying), preferably non-stick.  When it shimmers, add the patties, flour-side down.  Sprinkle the tops with a little more flour.'),
('7430', '7', 'Cook, undisturbed, until they form a crust and are easily flipped, 3 minutes per side.'),
('7430', '8', 'Serve with the sauce, which is just the mayonnaise mixed with remaining dill and garlic.'),
('7432', '1', 'Thaw fish, if frozen. Rinse fish. pat dry with paper towels.On a cutting board, spread each fish open, skin side down.In a small bowl stir together melted butter and lemon juice. Set half of the butter mixture aside.'),
('7432', '2', 'Brush remaining half of the butter mixture over fish.In a small bowl stir together onion, rosemary, lemon peel, salt, and pepper. Sprinkle onion mixture over fish.Fold fish closed.'),
('7432', '3', 'Place fish on a greased 15x10x1-inch baking pan.'),
('7432', '4', 'Bake in a 450 degree F oven for 15 minutes or until fish begins to flake when tested with a fork.If desired, sprinkle fish with parsley.'),
('7432', '5', 'Serve fish with lemon wedges and reserved butter mixture.'),
('7433', '1', 'Cut two large pieces of aluminium foil.'),
('7433', '2', 'Remove skin with knife.Slice the onions, place half of the sliced onions on first piece of aluminium, place the trouts over the onions.Top trouts with remaining onions, tarragon, butter (cut in small pieces).'),
('7433', '3', 'Pour heavy cream and wine over the trouts.Season with salt & pepper to taste.'),
('7433', '4', 'Place second aluminium foil over the prepared trouts and close tightly all around.Cook for 20 minutes at 350 or over the BBQ.Unwrap and serve with basmati or jasmin rice.'),
('7434', '1', 'Divide fish into 4 equal pieces if necessary.In shallow bowl, combine flour, lemon rind, thyme, salt and pepper.Dip fish into lemon juice. dredge in flour mixture, turning to coat.In nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. cook fish, turning once, for 6 to 8 minutes or until flakes easily when tested with fork.'),
('7436', '1', 'Clean trout and remove heads.Preheat grill to searing temperature around 400 degrees.Coat outside of trout with oil.Sprinkle salt and pepper on inside of trout.'),
('7436', '2', 'Add lemon juice to trout if desired.Reduce grill heat to medium or 250 degrees and place trout on grill.Trout cook quickly and should be flipped when grill side has just become white.Trout are finished when all meat is white and flaky (don''t over cook).'),
('7436', '3', 'Serve trout immediately.'),
('7437', '1', 'Fry bacon in a large heavy skillet over medium heat until crisp and golden brown, about 15 minutes.'),
('7437', '2', 'Drain on paper towels and set aside, reserving bacon fat in pan.Rinse fish, then dredge in cornmeal and season both sides to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('7437', '3', 'Add vegetable oil to the bacon fat, then heat pan over medium high heat until oil is hot.Working in batches if necessary, fry fish in combined fat and oil on one side until skin is golden and crisp, about 5 minutes.Carefully turn fish over and cook other side for 5 minutes more.'),
('7437', '4', 'Serve garnished with bacon.'),
('7439', '1', 'While the potatoes are still warm, combine them with the corn, onion, sun-dried tomatoes, and smoked fish. Make the vinaigrette by whisking together the vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt, and pepper in a small bowl and slowly whisking in the oil. add herbs, if you like. Toss the arugula with a little less than 1 Tbs. of the dressing to coat it lightly. Mound it on two plates or in two soup bowls. Toss the potato mixture with 2 to 3 Tbs. of the dressing and arrange on the arugula.'),
('7439', '2', 'Drizzle on any leftover dressing if you like.'),
('7442', '1', 'In a cup, combine the wine and mustard.'),
('7442', '2', 'Heat the butter and oil in a skillet and very lightly saut the trout on both sides.'),
('7442', '3', 'Remove to a warm platter (the fish will be partially cooked). In the same skillet put the garlic, the wine mixture, salt to taste, and the clams and simmer, removing the clams as they open. Return the clams and fish fillets to the skillet and continue cooking until the fish is done (a total time, including the saut, of 5 minutes for each  inch of thickness), adding some Fish Broth as needed to maintain a small amount of sauce in the skillet. Spoon the sauce over the fish, sprinkle with parsley, and serve.'),
('7442', '4', 'var article'),
('7442', '5', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('7442', '6', 'article'),
('7442', '7', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('7443', '1', 'Remove the fatty skin and bones from the fillets.'),
('7443', '2', 'Place the pecans in a food processor and pulse until the consistency of coarse meal.Season with salt and pepper and spread in a shallow dish.'),
('7443', '3', 'Mix the flour and paprika in a shallow dish.'),
('7443', '4', 'Whisk the water and eggs in a shallow bowl until blended.Coat the fillets with the flour mixture and shake off the excess.Dip in the egg mixture and shake off the excess.Coat with the ground pecans and press lightly to adhere.'),
('7443', '5', 'Pour enough peanut oil into a large skillet to measure ". Pan-fry the fillets in the hot oil for 2-3 minutes per side or until the fillets flake easily and are light brown.'),
('7443', '6', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('7443', '7', 'Combine the honey and butter in a microwave-safe bowl.Microwave for 1 minute and stir.'),
('7443', '8', 'Drizzle the glaze over the fillets and sprinkle with the parsley.'),
('7444', '1', 'If the trout are frozen, thaw.Rinse and dry the fish, removing the heads if you like.'),
('7444', '2', 'Cut 3 shallow gashes on each side of the fish.Rub fish with the salt and pepper, and arrange side by side in an oblong pan or dish.'),
('7444', '3', 'Mix wine, lemon juice, and rind.'),
('7444', '4', 'Pour the mixture over fish and let marinate for 2 hours, turning a few times.Use a double-hinged wire grill and spread the bay leaves over one side.'),
('7444', '5', 'Drain the trout and arrange over the bay leaves.'),
('7444', '6', 'Brush top with melted butter.Close the grill, and place it 5 inches over heat.Grill 20 minutes. turn rack several times and baste the fish with melted butter.Discard bay leaves.'),
('7444', '7', 'Serve fish with lemon quarters and grilled tomatoes.'),
('7444', '8', 'Serves 6-12.'),
('7445', '1', 'Spray a large skillet with olive oil-flavored cooking spray. set aside.In a large shallow dish, combine egg whites, milk, Creole seasoning and pepper sauce.'),
('7445', '2', 'Whisk egg whites until frothy.Blend in cornmeal. add trout fillets turning to coat.Set skillet over medium-high heat.When pan is hot, spray trout with cooking spray and cook sprayed-side down, 2 minutes.Spray side-facing up with cooking spray and turn fillets.Cook until fish pulls apart when tested with a fork, 1 to 2 more minutes.'),
('7445', '3', 'Serve with lemon wedges and extra hot sauce on the side.'),
('7446', '1', 'In a large skillet, saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.Stir in parsley.'),
('7446', '2', 'Remove mushrooms to a serving platter. keep warm.'),
('7446', '3', 'Combine flour and salt in a shallow dish. coat fillets with flour mixture on both sides.'),
('7446', '4', 'Add 2 tablespoons butter to the skillet. Cook trout over medium heat for 8-10 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork. arrange over mushrooms.For sauce, melt remaining butter in a small saucepan.Gradually stir in cream and lemon juice.Bring to a boil for 3-4 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.'),
('7446', '5', 'Serve over trout and mushrooms.'),
('7447', '1', 'To cook trout, wash and dry the fish inside and out and coat sides with a little olive oil.Slice mushrooms and place half in the bottom of a shallow baking dish.Salt and pepper fish, inside and out, to taste and place in dish on top of mushrooms.Sprinkle bread crumbs over fish along with the minced parsley, chopped garlic and the green onion.If using fresh lemons, squeeze 1 or 2 directly over the entire trout including the inside.Meanwhile melt butter, add to olive oil and the juice of 2 lemons.'),
('7447', '2', 'Pour slowly over fish saving about half of the mixture.'),
('7447', '3', 'Bake for 20-25 minutes at 375 degrees or until they are tender and bread crumbs are light brown.Fish is done when the meat flakes easily when a fork is inserted into the flesh and lifted up slightly.Just before the fish are done, saute 1-2 minutes , the remaining mushrooms in the sauce that is left and pour over top after placing trout on a serving plate.'),
('7447', '4', 'Garnish with a few lemon wedges and a few sprigs of fresh parsley.'),
('7447', '5', 'Serve this Italian Trout recipe with rice, or Italian pasta, and a vegetable.'),
('7449', '1', 'Rinse the trout under cold running water (or in the beautiful mountain lake/stream you caught them in).Pat dry.Sprinkle with salt and pepper (I take a zip lock baggie in my pack with salt/pepper/garlic powder mixed together).Melt the butter in a large heavy skillet on medium-high heat.Coat the trout in corn meal and shake off the excess.When the butter is melted, place the coated trout, flesh side down, in the skillet.Fry 4-5 minutes, then turn and fry 4-5 minutes or until the flesh is golden brown and flaky. (Trout may be seasoned with garlic or onion powder before frying if desired, I also take a lemon with me to squeeze over the top).'),
('7451', '1', 'Spread the cheese in a flat-bottomed dish large enough to hold a trout fillet.Dredge each fillet, flesh side down, in the cheese. Arrange the fillets, flesh side up, on a clean dry work surface and coat with additional cheese.'),
('7451', '2', 'Heat a heavy non-stick skillet sprayed lightly with non-stick cooking spray over medium-high heat. Arrange the fillets, flesh side down and not touching, in the hot skillet.cook for 3 minutes.Turn the fillets once. cook 2 minutes longer.'),
('7451', '3', 'Serve hot with lemon wedges.'),
('7452', '1', 'Preheat hot grill or barbecue. Slash skins of fish deeply three times on each side to let the heat permeate the flesh.'),
('7452', '2', 'Remove the heads if you like.'),
('7452', '3', 'Brush the fish lightly with oil, and season with salt and pepper both inside and out.Cook under grill or on barbecue for 4 minutes on each side, or until the skin is browned and the flesh feels firm.Melt the butter in a wide shallow pan, and fry the nuts quickly until toasted.'),
('7452', '4', 'Add the garlic and parsley, and fry the mixture briefly until the parsley darkens slightly.'),
('7452', '5', 'Add the lemon juice with more salt and pepper to taste and heat through.Put each trout on a warm serving plate, and spoon over cashew and garlic butter.'),
('7454', '1', 'Peel and halve all cucumbers lengthwise, then remove seeds, reserving 1 cup peel and 1/4 cup seeds.'),
('7454', '2', 'Cut cucumbers into 1 1/2x1/4-inch strips.'),
('7454', '3', 'Place in medium bowl. Finely chop reserved cucumber peel and seeds in processor.'),
('7454', '4', 'Add 1/4 cup of chopped peel mixture to bowl with cucumber strips.'),
('7454', '5', 'Whisk vinegar, dill, and honey in small bowl to blend.'),
('7454', '6', 'Add to cucumber strips and toss to coat.'),
('7454', '7', 'Using fork, mash avocado in another small bowl. mix in lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7454', '8', 'Add avocado to cucumber mixture and toss to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('7454', '9', 'Divide cucumber salad among 4 plates. Arrange smoked trout alongside.'),
('7454', '10', 'Garnish with dill sprigs.'),
('7455', '1', 'Using a very sharp knife, score the skin on both sides of the fish on the diagonal at 1-inch intervals.'),
('7455', '2', 'Place in a shallow dish.In a small bowl, stir together the chopped rosemary, chopped thyme and garlic paste. Rub the herb-garlic paste all over the outside and inside of the fish. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7455', '3', 'Pour the vermouth and olive oil over the fish, turn to coat and let stand for 30 minutes.Prepare a grill for direct grilling over medium-high heat.'),
('7455', '4', 'Brush and oil the grill grate and a fish-grilling basket, if desired.'),
('7455', '5', 'Remove the fish from the marinade. discard the marinade. Stuff the fish cavities with a few of the lemon slices and the rosemary and thyme sprigs.Arrange the fish on the grill or in the basket directly over medium-high heat. Grill, turning once, until nicely charred and cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes per side. During the last few minutes of grilling, grill the remaining lemon slices over the hottest part of the fire, turning once, until lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes per side.'),
('7455', '6', 'Transfer the fish to individual plates or a serving platter, garnish with the grilled lemon slices and serve immediately.'),
('7455', '7', 'Serves 6 to 8.Adapted from Williams-Sonoma On the Grill, by Willie Cooper (Oxmoor House, 2009).'),
('7456', '1', 'Toss the endive, shallots, and radishes in a large bowl. Toss with half of the dressing and season with salt and pepper. Divide the mixture among 4 plates and arrange the beets around the plate. Tear the trout fillets into bite-sized pieces and place on each salad. Top each with 1 tablespoon of the trout roe and serve.'),
('7456', '2', 'Whisk together lemon juice, vinegar, mayonnaise, mustards and salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Slowly whisk in the oil until emulsified and stir in the tarragon.'),
('7456', '3', 'Combine water, salt, and sugar in a large container and mix until the salt is completely dissolved.'),
('7456', '4', 'Add the fish, cover, and refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('7456', '5', 'Soak wood chips in water for at least 1 hour.'),
('7456', '6', 'Remove trout, rinse and dry thoroughly.'),
('7456', '7', 'Use a covered grill (charcoal, gas or electric) and preheat to about 200 degrees F. Cover'),
('7456', '8', 'heated coals with 1/3 of the hickory chips.'),
('7456', '9', 'Place fish, skin side down, on well-greased grill, about 4 inches from coals. Close grill hood and open vent to circulate smoke.'),
('7456', '10', 'Add additional hickory chips, as necessary. Smoke trout for approximately 20 minutes. Trout is done when the cut surface is golden brown and flakes easily with a fork.'),
('7457', '1', 'Wash and pat dry the fish and prick it with a fork.'),
('7457', '2', 'Mix all ingredients except the olive oil.'),
('7457', '3', 'Brush this mixture on fish.Marinade for two hours or overnight.'),
('7457', '4', 'Brush grill with a bit of the olive oil.Grill fish for a few minutes on each side until the fish flakes easily.'),
('7458', '1', 'Wash trout in cold water. Blot dry. Slash outside flesh diagonally, 2 or 3 cuts to each fish.'),
('7458', '2', 'Cut lemons in half. Using 1/2 lemon for each trout, gently rub with cut side of lemon, squeezing as you rub. Season inside and out with salt & pepper. Sprinkle 1 tsp rosemary leaves in the cavity of each fish.Bring wine, stock, butter, and onion to simmer in shallow skillet or roasting pan.'),
('7458', '3', 'Add fish and simmer 12-15 minutes. Cover and refrigerate, in pan, 1 hour.'),
('7458', '4', 'Remove fish carefully from liquid. Lift off skin. Store on bed of paper towels on platter covered with foil or plastic wrap.Refrigerate liquid separately.Just before serving, arrange trout on beds of lettuce on individual serving plates.'),
('7458', '5', 'Pour over each fish 1 teaspoon of poaching liquid.'),
('7458', '6', 'Serve with mustard mayonnaise.'),
('7459', '1', 'Lay fish in one layer in oven-proof dish.'),
('7459', '2', 'Combine remaining ingredients, pour over fish, and let stand 30 minutes.Turn and marinate 15 minutes longer.'),
('7459', '3', 'Bake in preheated 350F oven for 25 minutes or until fish is firm to the touch.OR Freeze fish with marinade in zip-lock bag.Thaw and bake as above.'),
('7460', '1', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('7460', '2', 'Pour beer into the pancake mix container in place of the water it calls for. Make the batter as thick or thin as you prefer. Close the lid, give it a few shakes, and boom it''s done.'),
('7460', '3', 'Dip fish into the batter using a pair of tongs, or if you want to dirty a dish, pour the batter in a bowl first. If you cut your fish into smaller pieces, you can toss them into the container, close the lid and shake it a couple of times, then carefully remove the coated pieces.'),
('7460', '4', 'Remove the fish from the batter using tongs, and place into the hot oil. Fry the fish until golden brown on both sides, 3 to 4 minutes per side.'),
('7461', '1', 'Cut the smoked fish into 1in (2.5cm) pieces.'),
('7461', '2', 'Place in a food processor and add the cheese, lemon juice, and horseradish. Pulse until smooth. Season with pepper and more horseradish if you wish. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, at least 1 hour and up to 24 hours.'),
('7461', '3', 'Transfer to a serving bowl and sprinkle with paprika.'),
('7461', '4', 'Good with melba toast, toasted slices of whole-grain bread, or chunks of baguette.'),
('7462', '1', 'line the grill pan with foil.'),
('7462', '2', 'Brush both trout with melted butter and grill both sides on a medium heat until the skin is CRISPY. Put fresh dill and toasted almond slices in the centre of the trout.Layer ONE side of the the trout with toasted almonds (this can be done easily by layering them on a flat tray under the grill until crisp, light brown and firm) to look like "scales"-place on 2 plates to rest.Boil a small tub of single cream with a table of lemon,salt and pepper to taste and a small pinch of sugar. Stir VIGOROUSLY constantly!'),
('7462', '3', 'Add a tsp of ground almonds, finely chopped dill, toasted almond flakes, salt and pepper to taste. Lay ON the plate with a serving spoon, lay the trout on top and then drizzle some more on the almond coated side of your trout.'),
('7462', '4', 'Serve IMMEDIATELY.'),
('7463', '1', 'In a medium skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil.'),
('7463', '2', 'Add the garlic and cook over moderately high heat until fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
('7463', '3', 'Add the wine and boil until reduced by half, about 1 minute.'),
('7463', '4', 'Add the chicken stock and boil until reduced by half again, about 1 minute.'),
('7463', '5', 'Remove the skillet from the heat and whisk in the cold butter, 1 tablespoon at a time.'),
('7463', '6', 'In another medium skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of the oil.'),
('7463', '7', 'Add the shiitake caps and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in the sesame seeds and cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned, about 1 minute. Season the shiitake with salt and pepper and remove the skillet from the heat.'),
('7463', '8', 'On a plate, toss the pumpkin seeds with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and the cayenne. Press the boned side of the trout fillets into the pumpkin seeds to coat.'),
('7463', '9', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil.'),
('7463', '10', 'Add the trout fillets, crusted side down, and cook over moderately high heat until browned, about 2 minutes. Turn the fillets and cook until the fish is just white throughout and the skin is crisp, about 3 minutes.'),
('7463', '11', 'Transfer the fillets to plates.'),
('7463', '12', 'Add the scallions, tomato, cilantro and lime juice to the sauce and rewarm over moderately high heat, stirring. do not let it boil. Spoon the sauted shiitake and the sauce over the trout and serve.'),
('7464', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Rinse fish, and pat dry.'),
('7464', '2', 'Rub fillets with olive oil, and season with garlic salt and black pepper.'),
('7464', '3', 'Place each fillet on a large sheet of aluminum foil.  Top with jalapeno slices, and squeeze the juice from the ends of the lemons over the fish. Arrange lemon slices on top of fillets. Carefully seal all edges of the foil to form enclosed packets.'),
('7464', '4', 'Place packets on baking sheet.'),
('7464', '5', 'Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes, depending on the size of fish. Fish is done when it flakes easily with a fork.'),
('7465', '1', 'Combine lemon grass, shredded lime leaves, rind and juice in a saucepan, bring to the boil, reduce heat simmer, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to 1 Tablespoon.Strain through a fine sieve into a medium heatproof bowl, cool 10 Min''s, discard solids.Set bowl over saucepan of simmering water, do not allow water to touch the base of the bowl, add egg yolk to juice mixture, whisk over heat until thickened.'),
('7465', '2', 'Remove bowl from heat, gradually add melted butter in a thin, steady stream, whisking constantly until sauce has thickened. (If sauce is too thick a tablespoon of hot water can be added.) stir in finely chopped kaffir lime leaves.Meanwhile, cook the fish on a heated oiled grill or fry pan until cooked as desired, serve with hollandaise. I prefer to cook my fish skin side down first and really get a nice crisp skin on it.'),
('7466', '1', 'Sprinkle trout with salt and pepper.Dust the fish filets in the flour.'),
('7466', '2', 'Heat the olive oil and butter on medium high heat.'),
('7466', '3', 'Add fish filets and cook until light brown on both sides.'),
('7466', '4', 'Remove from pan and cover to keep warm.Return pan to heat and add 1 T butter.'),
('7466', '5', 'Add the almonds and saute, then add the fresh lemon juice.'),
('7466', '6', 'Heat it through, then spoon over the fish filets.'),
('7466', '7', 'Serve with additional lemon wedges.'),
('7467', '1', 'To prepare the trout: Preheat the oven to 400F Coat a large baking sheet with oil.With a tweezer or pin-nosed pliers, remove any tiny bones from the fillets, skin side down, on the baking sheet.In a large saut pan, heat the oil over medium heat.'),
('7467', '2', 'Pour half into a cup. set aside.'),
('7467', '3', 'Add the scallions and carrot to the pan.Cook for about 3 minutes, or until soft.'),
('7467', '4', 'Add the bread cubes, broth, egg, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and the pepper.Toss to moisten.Spoon oval mounds of the stuffing on the fillets.Press lightly to pack.'),
('7467', '5', 'Drizzle with the reserved oil.'),
('7467', '6', 'Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until the stuffing is golden.With a panckae turner, transfer the stuffed fillets to plates.Note: This dish may be put together several hours in advance.Allow the stuffing to cool to room temperature before mounding the fillets.Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.The baking time may increase by 5 minutes.'),
('7468', '1', 'Finely chop parsley and garlic and put in medium bowl.'),
('7468', '2', 'Add all spices and 2 tablespoons oil. Toss together with hands.Chop potatoes into 1/3 inch thick circles. Chop tomatoes into quarters. Chop onion into 6 wedges. Chop bell peppers into large rings. Trim asparagus.Put all vegetables onto a large baking dish or tajine pan, there is no method to this just pile them on.'),
('7468', '3', 'Drizzle the rest of the olive oil over the veggies. At this point, take a little of all the spices used and lightly sprinkle over veggies (just a few pinches of each).Take the whole trout and stuff a small handful of the parsley mixture into each (this should be about a third of the mixture for all the fish) . Rub a little olive oil on the trout if you want to help it crisp the skin.Take a third of the parsley mixture and evenly coat the veggies on the pan. Lay the fish down on top of the veggies and cover the fish with the remaining parsley mixture.'),
('7468', '4', 'Bake in a preheated 400F oven for about an hour or until the fish is crisp on the outside and the veggies are browned and roasted.Enjoy!'),
('7469', '1', 'Mix first 5 ingredients, let stand for at least an hour.Prepare your fish, I fillet and spread mayo mix on meat.Wrap in foil, grill on med-high for 3-4 minutes on each side, depending on the size of my fish.'),
('7472', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees.Sprinkle a little bit of the vinegar on the fish filets, rinse them and pat them dry on a paper towel.Rub a little bit of salt into the filets.'),
('7472', '2', 'Place the fish into an oven safe casserole dish.On one side sprinkle the filets with half of the lemon juice and then coat them with half of the bread crumbs.Note if you need more than 1/3 of a cup of bread crumbs use them it''s up to your taste. I also used italian bread crumbs and they were very tasty.'),
('7472', '3', 'Drizzle the filets with olive oil. Make sure that all of the bread crumbs are coated in olive oil even if you need to use more than the suggested amount so that it crisps up nicely.Turn the filets over and repeat steps 5-7 with the remaining olive oil, lemon juice, and bread crumbs.Cover the fish and marinade at room temperature for 30 minutes.While the fish marinades, make the sauce by adding the thyme, lemon juice, mustard and salt to taste to a food processor and pulse for 1 minute.'),
('7472', '4', 'Add the butter and process until smooth.Slowly drizzle in the olive oil until the sauce fully incorperates into a smooth mayonnaise like consistency.After the fish has marinaded, place the casserole dish uncovered in the 400 degree oven. Again, cooking times may vary depending on what type of fish you use. I cooked the 6 oz 1-1 1/2 in thick salmon filets that I used for 13 minutes on each side, and then broiled them on one side for 2 minutes to give the crust some color. You could also grill the fish if you prefer.'),
('7472', '5', 'Serve the fish with the sauce drizzled over them.Enjoy!'),
('7473', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 200C'),
('7473', '2', 'Place fish in a shallow baking dish.'),
('7473', '3', 'Combine soy, ginger and sweet chilli sauce, then pour over fish.Cover with foil and bake for 8 minutes, or until just cooked through.'),
('7473', '4', 'Serve fish on rice, drizzled with sauce and garnished with spring onion.'),
('7474', '1', 'Remove skin if using fillets.'),
('7474', '2', 'Cut fish into serving size pieces.Season with seasoning salt and arrange in single layer in greased, shallow baking dish.'),
('7474', '3', 'Pour wine over and cover with aluminum foil.'),
('7474', '4', 'Bake at 450 for 10 min/inch of thickness or until opaque.'),
('7474', '5', 'Remove from oven and drain cooking liquid into small saucepan.Stir in remaining ingredients and heat until just warmed through.Spoon over fish and serve immediately.'),
('7475', '1', 'Soak green onion julienne in cold water. In a heatproof bowl, stir together chopped green onions and coriander. cover with ginger, 1 tsp (5 ml) of the salt, chilies and white pepper. In a small saucepan heat oil with Szechuan peppercorns over medium heat until fragrant. add sesame oil and pour through a strainer over green onion mixture. Stir until well mixed. cool.'),
('7475', '2', 'Pour most of the oil from the surface of the relish and reserve.'),
('7475', '3', 'Sprinkle fish with remaining salt and black pepper and grill or broil on both sides. For salmon darns, grill skinside first then flip and remove skin. (For trout, baste fish after turning with reserved oil and turn a second time to baste. ensure that skin is crispy.) When just cooked through, remove from grill. Cover each salmon piece with a line of the relish. (For trout, cut through skin with a sharp knife at the bottom of one side from the stomach opening to the tail. carefully peel back crispy skin in one piece and make a roll of it at the back of the fish. put a line of relish along the middle of the trout.)'),
('7475', '4', 'Garnish fish with coriander sprigs and well-drained green onion julienne.'),
('7475', '5', 'var article'),
('7475', '6', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('7475', '7', 'article'),
('7475', '8', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('7476', '1', 'Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees fahrenheit.'),
('7476', '2', 'Remove any visible bones and cut off the head and tail (if it hasn''t already been done for you) If using a poacher place the tray in the poacher, add 1/4 cup water and place your salmon in the tray skin side down.If you do not have a fish poacher (how many of us do?) you can use any oven safe pan large enough to hold your fish.Just crumple and crinkle a medium sized sheet of tin foil and place your fish on the foil skin side down.'),
('7476', '3', 'Add enough water to just come to the edge of the foil without spilling onto the fish (approx 1/3 cup).On top of the fish sprinkle all ingredients.Cover with lid or tin foil.Cook for 12-20 min''s.For RARE fish, cook just until white liquid emerges from fish (this is the cooked fish oil).It will be pinky white on the outside and peachy pink inside.For more well done fish, cook until fish is a pinky white color all the way through.'),
('7476', '4', 'Place on a platter to serve.Leave onions, capers and dill on the fish.Slice lemons on the side for those who like fresh lemon juice.This salmon is great served with rice and steamed veggies or a salad.'),
('7477', '1', 'Whisk together the vinaigrette, lemon zest, garlic, and oregano in a medium bowl. Arrange the tuna steaks in a shallow baking dish and pour 1/2 cup of the mixture over them. Turn the tuna to coat, then cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('7477', '2', 'Heat a grill to high or a grill pan to medium-high. Grill about 4 minutes per side for medium-rare, depending on the heat level. Meanwhile, pour the remaining 1/4 cup of vinaigrette over the tomatoes, capers, and arugula and toss.'),
('7477', '3', 'Serve the tomato salsa over or alongside the tuna.'),
('7478', '1', 'Fill large bowl with ice water and lemon slices.'),
('7478', '2', 'Place sushi mat on cutting board with slats running crosswise. Arrange 1 sheet nori, shiny side down, on mat, lining up long edge of sheet with edge of mat nearest you. Lightly moisten hands with lemon water, then gently spread about 3/4 cup rice onto nori in even layer, leaving 1/2-inch border on long end opposite you.'),
('7478', '3', 'Brush 1/2 teaspoon wasabi paste in thin horizontal line across rice about 1 inch from side nearest you. Arrange about 1/8 of tuna strips in horizontal line atop wasabi line, cutting tuna as necessary to fit from side to side.'),
('7478', '4', 'Beginning with edge nearest you, lift mat up with thumbs, holding filling in place with fingers, and fold mat over filling so that upper and lower edges of rice meet. Squeeze gently but firmly along length of roll and tug top edge of mat away from you to tighten. (Nori border will still be visible below top edge of mat.) Open mat and roll log forward 1/4 turn, then fold mat over again and squeeze gently but firmly to seal nori border. Repeat to form remaining rolls.'),
('7478', '5', 'Transfer 1 roll, seam side down, to cutting board. Dip sharp knife into lemon water, shaking off excess. Slice roll in half, then cut each half into 3 pieces. Slice remaining rolls in same manner.'),
('7478', '6', 'Serve immediately with remaining wasabi paste, ginger, daikon, carrots, and soy sauce.'),
('7483', '1', 'Combine tuna, celery, carrots, onion, mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.'),
('7483', '2', 'Heat a large skillet over low heat. Spray skillet with oil, and place two slices of bread on top. Top bread with cheese, then tuna salad and tomato. Cook on low heat until cheese melts and bread gets toasty.'),
('7483', '3', 'Serve immediately.Print This5 SP 6 PP Lunch Recipes Sandwich Recipes Under $10posted August 31, 2010 by Gina58 Comments'),
('7484', '1', 'Use a vegetable peeler to peel the zest off the lemon. Use a sharp knife to cut the zest into long thin strips.Rub the tuna steaks with the garlic, and then sprinkle both sides with the salt and pepper.'),
('7484', '2', 'Put the steaks in a large freezer bag, and then scatter the lemon zest across them.'),
('7484', '3', 'Drizzle the olive oil all over the tuna, and seal the bag, pressing out as much air as you can.'),
('7484', '4', 'Put the tuna in the fridge overnight to marinate.When you are ready to grill the steaks, take them out of the fridge while you heat up the grill (about 15 minutes). The grill should be very hot when you put them on. Grill one side until you see the red tuna turn beige about 1/3 of the way up the side. Flip, then grill the other side until you can only see a hint of pink from the side.'),
('7484', '5', 'Serve the tuna steaks with a salad.'),
('7487', '1', 'Roughly chop the onion, squash, peppers, and celery. Pulse in a food processor to mince.'),
('7487', '2', 'Heat 3 tablespoons of the oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('7487', '3', 'Add the minced vegetables, 1 teaspoon of the salt, and the cayenne. Cook, stirring frequently, until the vegetables are soft and the liquid has evaporated, about 5 minutes.'),
('7487', '4', 'Add the tomatoes, Worcestershire, and hot sauce. Bring the liquid to a boil, reduce heat, and simmer about 25 minutes, stirring frequently. Meanwhile, prepare the rice according to the package directions. Season both sides of the tuna with the remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and the black pepper.'),
('7487', '5', 'Heat the remaining oil in a large skillet and sear the tuna on both sides, working in batches if necessary, until the flesh is just pink in the center, about 6 minutes total. Arrange the tuna over the rice and cover with the Creole vegetable sauce.'),
('7488', '1', 'In a non-reactive bowl combine soy, honey, and wasabi powder. Reserve 1/4 cup for dipping sauce.'),
('7488', '2', 'Roll each piece of tuna in this mixture to coat evenly. Marinate from 1 hour to overnight.'),
('7488', '3', 'Remove the tuna from the marinade and discard the marinade.'),
('7488', '4', 'On a plate, lay the sesame seeds.'),
('7488', '5', 'Roll the tuna in the seeds to evenly coat.'),
('7488', '6', 'Fire up the chimney and top with a well-oiled grate. Sear for 15 to 30 seconds per side or to desired temperature.'),
('7488', '7', 'Remove to rack and rest for 3 minutes. Cover with foil or plastic wrap to achieve carry over cooking. Slice thinly and serve with the dipping sauce.'),
('7489', '1', 'Brush both sides of tuna with olive oil. sprinkle with seasoning. Saut or grill over medium-high heat 5 to 7 minutes or until desired degree of doneness. (Fish can also be baked or broiled.)'),
('7489', '2', 'Let stand 5 minutes, and slice.'),
('7489', '3', 'Spread one-fourth of the hummus evenly over each tortilla.'),
('7489', '4', 'Place spinach on hummus. Arrange roasted bell pepper and tuna evenly over spinach.'),
('7489', '5', 'Roll wrap, and serve immediately. If serving later, wrap in plastic wrap and chill.'),
('7489', '6', 'Note: Look at color first when shopping for tuna. Steaks range from pink to deep red, depending on the species. Never purchase tan or brown tuna. A darker band running along large loin pieces is perfectly normal but may have a strong taste. You can substitute many kinds of seafood--or even chicken--for tuna in this sandwich. For a healthy boost, try grilled salmon.'),
('7489', '7', 'Wine note: The newly released Beaulieu Vineyard Coastal Estates Pinot Grigio offers delicate floral aromas with peach and melon notes. This lighter white wine pairs well with the ahi, hummus, and bell pepper flavors. Or try Beaulieu''s Sauvignon Blanc, a natural match with the lean, clean taste of the tuna. It also complements the creamy yogurt and aromatic mint in the side dishes.'),
